âœ… Advice
Always use double brackets [[ ]] for multiple columns.

Avoid df.Name if the column has spaces or special characters.

                                        âœ… Chapter 7: Filtering Rows and Columns with Conditions
ðŸ”¹ Filter Rows with Condition
python
Copy
Edit
df[df['Age'] > 25]
df[df['Gender'] == 'Male']
ðŸ”¹ Filter with Multiple Conditions
python
Copy
Edit
df[(df['Age'] > 25) & (df['Gender'] == 'Male')]
ðŸ”¹ Select Specific Rows and Columns
python
Copy
Edit
df.loc[df['Age'] > 25, ['Name', 'Age']]
âœ… Real-Life Benefit
Extract customer segments

Find high-value transactions

Create rule-based insights (e.g., â€œall students with grade > 90â€)

âœ… Advice
Use .loc for conditional column selection

Always wrap conditions in parentheses () when using & or |


